# **Cross-Account Billing Read-Only Access Setup (Account A → Account B)**

## **Use Case :** 

You have full access to Account A. You need billing read-only access to Account B (client account) using AssumeRole and CloudFormation. No IAM user will be created in Account B.

## **Architecture Flow :** 

Login  →  Account A (main)   →  Switch role  →   Account B (client)  →  Open Billing (read only)

##   **Where to Run CloudFormation :**

CloudFormation stack must be deployed in Account B (client account).

##  **Permissions Required :**

Account A:

         \- Admin/root or IAM with sts:AssumeRole permission

Account B:

             \- Admin/root to deploy CloudFormation  
  \- Enable IAM access to Billing

##  **Steps in Account B (Client)**

1\.      Login to Account B

2\.      Go to Billing → Account settings → Enable IAM access to billing

3\.      Open CloudFormation → Create Stack

4\.      Upload provided template

![][image1]

 

   **Template file** :   
       [billing-cross-account.yaml](https://drive.google.com/file/d/1c7o75qlvA0tkITByp7YcXvADhHZypDPP/view?usp=drive_link)

5\.      Enter Account A ID as parameter

      \- During stack creation, you will be prompted to enter the **AccountAId** parameter.

      \- In this field, enter the AWS account ID of the **source account** — the account from

![][image2]

6\.      Create stack and wait for CREATE\_COMPLETE

## **Steps in Account A**

7\.      Login to Account A

8\.     Click Switch Role

\- In the AWS Management Console, click the account name in the top-right corner.  
\- Select **Switch Role**.

                     ![][image3]

9\.     Enter Account B ID and Role Name

Enter the following details:

    **Account ID:** The target/client account ID (Account B)  
    **Role name:** The role created by the CloudFormation stack  
    **Display name:** Optional label

![][image4]

10\.  Switch and access Billing console
